Post.title: git and git commit order
Post._content:
#### git order
```shell
#httpsclone
git clone https://github.com/YourGitHubName/RepositoriesName.git

#SSHclonessh key
git clone git@github.com:YourGitHubName/RepositoriesName.git

#,branchName
git clone git@github.com:YourGitHubName/RepositoriesName.git -b branchName

#
git status

#
git add -A

#
git rm filepath

#
git commit -m 'commit comments'

#
git push -u origin master

#
git branch -a

#
git branch newBranchName

#
git checkout branchName

#
git remote -v

#
#https,YourGitHubName=GitHubRepositoriesName=
git remote add origin https://github.com/YourGitHubName/RepositoriesName.git
#SSH
git remote add origin git@github.com:YourGitHubName/RepositoriesName.git

#(system,global,local)
git config --list

#
git config --system --list

#
git config --global --list

#
git config --local --list

#update
git stash

#
git stash save 'stash comments'

#
git checkout fileName
```

#### git commit rules
> *type*
> + fix/toBUGfixdifftodifffix
> + feat
> + refactorBUG
> + style
> + perf
> + docs
> + test
> + chore
> + revert
> + merge
> + syncBUG
>

Post.title: Hello World
Post._content:
Welcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).

## Quick Start

### Create a new post

``` bash
$ hexo new "My New Post"
```

More info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)

### Run server

``` bash
$ hexo server
```

More info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)

### Generate static files

``` bash
$ hexo generate
```

More info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)

### Deploy to remote sites

``` bash
$ hexo deploy
```

More info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html)

Post.title: linux order
Post._content:
```shell
#create folder
mkdir folderName

#create fileName
touch fileName

#check memory
free -h

#check hard disk
df -h

#copy file
cp /sourceFloder/fileName /tagetFloder/fileName

#modify file name
mv oldFileName newFileName

#console log,-f option is real time log
tail -fn 2000 /floder/log.log
```

```shell
#hexorootEACCESS

sudo su

npm install -g hexo-cli
```

hexo
```shell
#inithexo
hexo init ~/Documents/hexo

#npm
cd ~/Documents/hexo

npm install
```
